modules.description: This module provides precise timekeeping functionality using POSIX clocks, specifically returning the current time as a pair of days and picoseconds since the Unix epoch. It supports retrieving the current time zone offset in seconds and the clock's period in days and picoseconds, enabling accurate time measurements and adjustments. Concrete use cases include timestamping events with high precision, calculating time intervals, and synchronizing clocks across distributed systems.

Provides access to a monotonic clock via `elapsed_ns` to measure time intervals in nanoseconds and `period_ns` to determine the clock's resolution. Works with 64-bit integers to represent time values. Useful for precise timing measurements in virtualized environments, such as profiling code execution or tracking event durations.
